<br>
They are immune magically to one kind of magic (basically)<br>
<br>
Fire: Fire immune<br>
Earth: Disease immune<br>
Air: Cold immune<br>
Water: Poison immune<br>
<br>
The air pet is also somewhat magic resistant. Or at least, good at resisting partially. Fighting a necro, used an earth pet, fire pet, and air pet. Of course all the pets got feared and I got owned. However, using my air pet, I noticed one very important thing. Whereas my other pets would be feared and STAY feared throughout the fight, my air pet would break the fear within 5-10 seconds, and go back to pummeling on the Necro. What that means, I don't know, but my air pet has also resisted Gravity Flux spells in Seb when I have not.<br>
<br>
Fighting last night in Fungus Grove (small group, 52 warrior, 59 sk, 55 mage (me) and 60 druid). Druid pulls 3 shrooms. I DS the group, we seperate the mobs and each tank gets one, my earth pet tanks one. Now, these shrooms slow, BUT.. knowing your pet, and having known my earth pet would not be affected by a disease based slow, while the tanks (unhasted) were beating on their shrooms, I was laying waste to mine, and even DoTing theirs, to help them along. Guess who won their respective fight first? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I finishd out first, the SK next (fairly quick succession, though I think his shroom was caught in my Sirroco spell, twice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), then we all ganged up on the 52 warrior's shroom and gave it a dirt nap. This wasn't a Greater Vocerate pet, either, but just the little 51 earth pet. The healer also wound up out of mana through the fight, to add to our difficulties.<br>
<br>
Magicians IN RAIDS suffer because of the inability to use pets on the raid. Magicians in Experience groups still dish out quite a bit of damage, and unlike a melee, we can spread our damage out where it's needed most, or slaughter one creature as fast as possible. What's needed isn't necessarily higher damage for our pets, but rather, Better Pathing (or better AI for pathing), the ability to use our potent pet power more often (vs fearing mobs, vs dispelling mobs, on indoor areas, vs AoE mobs). /pet hold.. kind of does this. Not really, as you have to get 59 before you can get it. Quick summoning.. kind of helps. Vs AoE mobs, disperse your pet, choose one of the type that's comming in, and in 5 seconds, you've got a big bad tank ready to beat it into oblivion, tailored to resist the mob's AoE.<br>
<br>
Know your class, know what you can do, and for heavens sake, show what you can do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Warriors are often called for because they're simple to understand. Magicians aren't, but our skills are harder to grasp, harder to get used to, and certainly, more potent because of that difficulty once you get in the groove <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Rhasin Firestorm<BR>
Conjurer of the 55th Season<BR>
